=============================================================================
JIRA CEPH-571 Reject late multipart parts after upload completion

Developer: @vgoot
Code Review: @schiu 

[Description]
Prevents lagged parts from being recorded after an MPU is finished, eliminating stale part leakage and index pollution.
- Uses existing meta ref for the subsequent part-info update.
- Ensure the multipart upload still exists before we persist any part state;
- Guard multipart part uploads by stat’ing the multipart meta object before writing part data;
- If the meta object is gone (completed/aborted), surface NoSuchUpload early and skip writing the part.
- On rejection or error, the writer’s cleanup path purges any raw part objects created for the failed attempt.

[Issue]
MPU is created → MPU index entry exists
Parts upload in parallel
One part is slow and remains “in flight”
Client retries the same part number
Retry succeeds and is recorded as the valid part
Client calls CompleteMultipartUpload
RGW:
- Finalizes the MPU
- Removes MPU index entry
- Commits final object
But the original in-flight part object:
- Get accepted on completion but it is no longer referenced by MPU index
- Never gets cleaned up due to race timing,

Result: a detached multipart part object that inflates disk usage and billing.

{Repro]
Script to create phantom part: mpu_lag.py
1) Create MPU
2) Upload N parts in parallel
3) Make one part upload intentionally slow ("lagging")
4) While slow upload is still running, retry SAME PartNumber with a fast upload
5) Complete MPU using the fast retry's ETag for that PartNumber
6) Let the original slow upload finish AFTER completion (to exercise inconsistent index / phantom-part behavior)

Usage example:
"""
    # upload MPU in 4 chunks, each chunk of 6mb size, chunk 3 goes with slow and retry path 
    python3 mpu_lag.py --endpoint $EP   --access-key $AK  --secret-key $SK --bucket $B --key $KEY --parts 4 --part-size-mb 6 --lag-part 3 --lag-sleep-ms 10 --retry-after-sec 1
"""
command to validate/fix invalid parts entries 
"""
  # validate 
  radosgw-admin bucket check --bucket=vgoot-b-16  | jq .invalid_multipart_entries
  # fix
  radosgw-admin bucket check --bucket=$B --fix{code}
"""

